Number Formatting (Essential for readability)
Bulk Buying (Major quality of life)
Achievement System (Engagement driver)
Prestige Mechanics (Long-term retention)
Polish & Audio (Final touches)

Chouta Consumption System

 Orders consume Chouta/sec (they need food like any army)
 Bridgemen consume Chouta/sec (higher consumption, they do dangerous work)
 Consumption scales with numbers (10 Windrunners = 10x food cost)
 Starvation penalties: Unfed units produce less or go inactive
 Efficiency upgrades: Better cooking reduces consumption per unit

Sphere Payment System

 Orders require Sphere payments (weekly/daily wages)
 Payment tiers: Higher order abilities need higher sphere denominations
 Wage inflation: More experienced orders demand better spheres
 Payment strikes: Unpaid orders refuse to work or leave
 Loyalty bonuses: Well-paid orders work harder

Sphere Economics Redesign
Sphere as Currency Flow (Not Capped Storage)
